Description: This painting was sent to the Museo de Pintura (later Museo de Bellas Artes) when Valenzuela Puelma was studying on a government grant in Paris (1883). It is listed among the works  exhibited in the 1891 Salon de Bellas Artes, Santiago.  Valenzuela Puelma's son is thought to have been one of the models.

Name_Title: El Descendimiento de la Cruz
Creator: Arías Cruz, Virginio
Description: Marble statue. Purchased by the government for the Museo de Bellas Artes, Santiago, in 1890 for 30,000 francs. The statue won third prize at the Salón de los Artistas Franceses (1887), a gold first class at the 1899 Paris Exposition, and a first at the Buffalo Pan-American Exhibition in 1901. Listed in 1891 Museo de Bellas Artes, Santiago, Catalogue.

Name_Title: Plano del Rio Maullin i Sus Tributarios Formado por la Comision esploradora de Chiloé i Llanquihue bajo la direccion del C. G. de Fta. Francisco Vida
Creator: Vidal Górmaz, Francisco
Description: Note reads: El Rio Maullin i sus tributarios esperimentan el flujo: El reflujo de las mareas del Oceano, alcanzando la influencia de éstas hasta los puntos marcados T en la parte superior de cada rio. Este signo indica tambien navegable de cada uno de los tributarios, menos en el Maullin que permite su aceso hasta el Salto, este es, 25 quilómetros mas arriba de la isla Ortuzar. Ese trecho es correntoso, bien encajonado, profundo i accesible con algun trabajo, empleando bongos i bogadores locales.Los números de la sonda representan metros i fracciones de éste i los números colocados sobre el terreno la altura absoluta del lugar que ocupan. Advertencia La entrada al río, Maullín, no es peligrosa ordinariamente, empleando balandras o buenos botes, pero no debe intentarse con bravera de mar de fuera porque entonces la boca rompe mucho con olas mui arbolados. En todo caso, ninguna embarcacion debe aventurarse a entrar sin  llevar consigo un prática que puede tomar en Ancud, Carelpapu o Puerto Godoy.Rio Quenuir:

Name_Title: El Río Cachapoal
Creator: Smith, Antonio
Description: The painting dates from 1870 but it is unknown when arrived at Museo de Bellas Artes (Santiago de Chile).

Name_Title: Retrato de Don Francisco Casimiro Marco del Pont
Creator: Bourgeois, Virginia
Description: This portrait was part of the Governor Series Vicuña Mackenna commissioned for the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873) in Santiago de Chile. It won an honourable mention in 1874 in Concurso de Retratos de Gobernadores, primera serie. Bourgeois was a student at the Academia de Pintura when she painted this portrait.The caption at bottom reads, 'Un esbirro afeminado que habia estado en el sitio de Zaragoza pero debió su baston jeneral de Chile al influjo de su hermano don Juan José Marcó uno de los jefes del partido absolutista en Españs.  Fue cobarte cruel i no supo sobrellevar sus desgracias, por consejos de un fraile mando construir esta fortaleza, en la cual figura su retrato como ultimo de los gobernadores de España en 1810' 1873.

Name_Title: Don Diego de Almagro
Creator: Mesa, Domingo
Description: This painting is a copy of one that was part of the Governors' Series Benjamìn Vicuña Mackenna commissioned for the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873) in Santiago de Chile. Donated by the Municipality of Santiago. Caption reads, ' Descubridor de Chile, natural de Almagro en Castilla la vieja, nació por el año de 1463, descubrió a Chile en 1535 i habiendo llegado hasta el valle de Melipilla, regresó al Cuzco donde fue traidoramente ejectuado por su émulo i compañero de conquistas el 8 de Julio de 1539' 1873.

Name_Title: Don Fransico de Villagra
Creator: Carmona, Pedro Leon
Description: This painting was part of the Governors' Series Benjamìn Vicuña Mackenna commissioned for the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873). Caption reads, 'Segundo gobernador propietario de Chile. Vino a Chile con Pedro de Valdivia i fue uno de sus más esforzados capitanes i leales amigos. Fue dos veces gobernador interino en 1543 i en 1551 entro a gobernar en propiedad el 10 de julio de 1561'. Carmona was a student at the Academia de Pintura when this painting was done. 1873.

Name_Title: Don Rodrigo de Quiroga
Creator: Ortega, José Mercedes
Description: This painting is part of the Governor Series Vicuña Mackenna commissioned for the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873). Caption reads, 'Tercer gobernador de Chile. Era natural de masinos, Galicia en España fue paje de la condesa de lemos, compañero de Don Pedro de Valdivia. Hallose en la fundación de Santiago. Fue tres veces gobernador y falleció desempeñando el cargo en 1580. En los años de su gobiernos se instalo en Chile la real audiencia'. Ortega was a student at the Academia de Pintura at the time of painting (1873).

Name_Title: Don Martin García Oñez de Loyola
Creator: Salinas, first name uncertain
Description: This painting is part of the Governor Series Vicuña Mackenna commissioned for the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873) and painted that same year.  It was donated to the museum by the Municipality.Caption reads, 'Sobrino de San Ignacio i casi su contemporáneo. Era un capitán temerario i su muerte a manos de los bárbaros, como la de Valdivia, fue la señal del gran alzamiento que redujo a cenizas 'Las Siete Ciudades'. Gobernó desde 1592 a 1598'.

Name_Title: Retrato de Don Manuel Amat y Juniet
Creator: Anon.
Description: This painting is part of the Governor Series Vicuña Mackenna commissioned for the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873) and was painted that same year. On the back is painted, 'Don Manuel Anat y Juniet. Gobernador de Chile /1753-1764)'

Name_Title: Tomás de Azuá Itorgoyen
Creator: Anon.
Description: Copy of a painting shown at the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873). The original was painted in 1873.  The portrait depicts the first rector of the University, which is where the original now resides.

Name_Title: Pianoforte
Creator: Anon.
Description: Exhibited in the Esposicion de Coloniaje. Made in Lima and on inside says, 'Fabricado en Lima en 1785 para el uso de la Señora Rivero Aguirre y Guerrero. 1785 de lo serena el que (illegible)'.

Name_Title: La Fundación de Santiago
Creator: Lira, Pedro
Description: The painting, dating from 1888, was exhibited at the 1889 Paris Universial Exposition, where it won a 2nd medal. It was purchased by the government for $4,000.The moment depicted is Pedro de Valdivia's founding of the city in 1541 onto of the Cerro de Santa Lucia.

Name_Title: Retrato de Don José A. de Manso y Velasco
Creator: Anon.
Description: This painting is part of the Governor Series Vicuña Mackenna commissioned for the Esposicion de Coloniaje (1873) and was painted the same year. It was also exhibited in the Museo Histórico-Indigena at Santa Lucia, in 1875. The caption reads, ' Exmo D. Joseph Manso de Velasco y Samaniego. Conde de Superunde Cavallero del hábito de Santiago. Virrey del Perú. Teniente de los Reales Exercitos. Provifto Gobernador del Reyno de Chile. Prefidente de fu Real Audiencia. Nació en Logroño (Castilla la Viexa) 1688. Murió en Granada 1745. Por cedula del Catolico monarca Filipo sus restos fueron depositados bajo el altar mayor en el monasterio del los monjes de Calathrava'.

Name_Title: Retrato de Don Ambrosio O'Higgins
Creator: Anon.
Description: The painting dates from 1795, and was done in Lima. It was exhibited at the Esposicion del Coloniaje, 1873 Santiago

Name_Title: Retrato de Tomás de Figueroa y Caravaca

Description: This is a 1930 copy of a painting from the Esposicion del Coloniaje, 1873. The original is in Spain with the Figueroa family.

Name_Title: Tipos de escravos do Rio de Janeiro
Creator: Freitas Henriques Jr., José Christiano de  (Christ
Description: Presentation card ('carte de visite') featuring a 'typical' black slave, from the homonymous series ('Types of slaves of Rio de Janeiro'). These picture-cards, with their nostalgic evocation of urban slavery, became extremely popular in the late 1880s, especially after the definitive abolition of slavery in 1888.

Name_Title: Arraial dos Canudos
Creator: Urpia, D
Description: Bird's eye picture-map of the town of Canudos in the State of Bahia, Brazil, from the year in which it was seized and destroyed by the Federal Army, killing most of its inhabitants. Previous military expeditions had been overthrown by the town's millenarist and anti-republican inhabitants, in a four-years war that inspired Euclides da Cunha's epic masterpiece "Os sertões" (English ed.: "Rebellion in the Backlands), 1902. The caption reads: "Arraial dos Canudos, vista pela estrada do Rosário, escolhida pela Expedição Moreira César, segundo informações administradas pelo Dr. Américo Passo, cnel. José Américo Camilo de Souza Velho, e de acordo com os dois oficiais de policía que fizeram parte da expedição  Moreira César, reconhecido como cópia fiel da povoação por toda a força da policía e por mais pessoas insospeitas" Legend reads: 0 - Estrada do Cambaio 1 - Casa abandonada 3 - Doentes onde falheceu Moreira César 4 - Posição tomada perlo 16. Batalhão 5 - Igreja nova 6 - Posição do 7. Batalhão 7 - Jardim com grade de ferro 8 - Santuário novo 9 - Igreja velha 10 - Casas caiadas, portas verdes, comércio 11 - Rua onde entrou a força de polica 12 - Cercado onde colocou-se a cavalaria 13 - artilheria 14 - Cerca abombada pela policía 15 Rio Basabarres 16 - Grandes árvores

Creator: Giunji, Ignacio
Description: A bust of the Jesuit who was expelled from Chile in 1767. In the following years, Molina's writing on  natural history made Chile better known in Europe. The bust had been held in Bologna, Italy, before Santiago's mayor Benjamín Vicuña Mackenna brought it to Chile. The bust was exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exposition, Santiago.

Name_Title: Portrait of Domingo Eyzaguirre Archavale
Creator: Moinvoisin, Raymond
Description: Known for his simplicity (evidence by his suit), Eyzaguirre was involved in an irrigation project in the Maipo flood plain. He is depicted here with the plan for the Maipo canal in his hands. He was also a well-known philanthropist. The portrait was exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exposition, Santiago.

Name_Title: Portrait of Domingo Eyzaguirre Archavale
Creator: Moinvoisin, Raimundo

He is depicted here with the plan for the Maipo canal in his hands. He was also a well-known philanthropist. The portrait was exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exposition, Santiago.

Name_Title: **O último baile da monarquia na Ilha Fiscal
Creator: de Figueiredo e Melo, Aurélio
Description: Nascido na Parha, o autor deste quadro, Francisco Aurélio de Figueiredo e Melo, era irmão do pintor Pedro Américo, de quem foi aluno na Academia Imperial de Belas Artes, tendo se dedicado também a caricatura, a escultura e a literatura.  Pintou temas históricos, paisagens e retratos.  Este quadro, que o autro chamou de ‘A Ilusão do Terceiro Reindao’, representa o baile realizado em 9 de novembro de 1889, no Palácio da Guarda-Mor, na Ilha Fiscal, em homenagem aos oficiais do encouraçado chileno Almirante Cochrane.  O baile foi promovido pelo Presidente do Conselho de Ministros, Visconde de Ouro Preto, el pelo Ministro dos Negócios estrangeiros, José Francisco Diana, tendo se constituído na última festa da monarquia.  A pintura foi elaborada em 1905, conm autorização do Congresso Federal e adquirida pelo Presidente Rodrígues Alves.  A obra é composta por trés grandes planos na base e duas representações imaginadas, lembrando a movimentação de um panorama.  Vé-se a chegada dos convidados e as personalidades ligadas ao poder imperial, no cais da ilha, tendo ao fundo as embarcações ancoradas na baía de Guanabara, com a Cidade do Rio de Janeiro num ultimo plano.  Na extremidade superior direita Aurélio de Figueiredo evocou uma possível coroação de Princesa Isabel, como Imperatriz, enquanto na extremidade superior esquerda alude à marcha de uma República triunfante, o que de fato aconteccu alguna dias após o baile.

Name_Title: Portrait of Pedro de Valdivia
Creator: Anon., a copy of a work done by 'Lucas'
Description: The painting was donated to Chile by Isabel II in 1856. It was exhibited in 1873 Santiago Colonial Exhibition. The caption reads, 'Lereso capitán, natural de la Serena en estremadura, conquistó i pobló a Chile hasta Valdivia fundó a Santaigo el 12 de febrero de 1541 i murió en la batalla de Tucupal en enero de 1554. Gobernó desde 1540 a 1554.

Name_Title: Un Rincón del Museo en el Palacio de Bellas Artes
Creator: Formas de Dávila, Ema
Description: The interior of the history musem, while it was still sharing space with the Museo de Bellas Artes in Santiago. Donated by the artist to the Museo Histórico in 1952

Name_Title: Retrato de Don Manuel Alday y Axpe
Creator: Legarda, José
Description: This painting from 1772 was owned by Monseñor José Ignacio Victor Eyzaguirre, exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exhibition and came from the Biblioteca Nacional to the museum in 1911. The caption reads, 'El Ilmo Sr. Dn. Manuel de Aldai y Axpeé natural de la Ciudad de la Concepcion de Chile, fue delegado general de la Santa Cruzada en Aquel reino. Fue promovido al obispo de dicha cathedral de Santiago, y tomo su posesion por agosto de 1755, desde el siguiente contribuie 5000 pesos cada año para la fabrica de su nueva cathedral, ofsitio al concilio provincial de Lima principiado por enero de 1772 y dixo la oracion el dia de fu apertura'. The book on the table is labelled, 'decretales'.

Name_Title: Retrato de Don Diego Portales Palazulo
Creator: Domeniconi, Camilo
Description: The painting, commissioned by the government, dates from 1837. Domeniconi a 'mediocre' Italian painter. Portales is wearing the uniform of a lieutenant coronel, and he's surrounded by 'emblems of his power and political plans'. Exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exposition, and comments taken from the catalogue. Exhibit num. 75.

Name_Title: Retrato de Don José Migual Infante
Creator: Moinviosin, Raimundo
Description: The painting dates from 1844. Infante was a lawyer and figure in the Indepdence struggles. Congress commissioned the painting and ordered it to be hung in the main hall of the Palacio de Gobierno. Exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exposition,num. 98.

Name_Title: La Batalla de Chabanco
Creator: Vandorse, Thomás
Description: This painting is from the same schools as Rugendas, and copied his style of the 'Batalla de Maipo'. Painted in 1850

Name_Title: Piano
Description: Painoforte of Doña Luisa Esterripa de Muñoz Guzmán. Made in London. A card inside reads, 'Para el uso de Da Luisa Muñoz de Guzmán. Por Muzio Clementi, Londres Año 1814' Two pianos were exhibited in the Colonial Exhibition, but this does not appear to be either of those.

Name_Title: Retrato de Don Alonso del Pozo y Silua
Creator: Anon.
Description: 18th century painting, uncertain who the person in the background is. Among one of the few Chilean bishops. The caption reads, 'Retrato de Ilust. señor Alonso del Pozo y Silva, natural de la Concepción. celejial en este convictorio de S. Francisco Xavier, cura de la ciudad de Chillán. Canónigo magistral de su obispado, y en dicha iglesia de la Concepción subio este el deanato. De alli fue promovido al obispado de Córdova de donde acencio a este de Santiago y del él al arzobispado de la Plata, donde despues de haber governado algunos años renunció y se retiró a vivir a esta ciudad, donde murio en 17 de sepe de 1725 años con mucho opinion de santidad. Fue sepultado en el colegio maximo de la Compañía de Jesús en esta capital de Santiago de Chile. Colonial Exhibition 1873, num. 44

Name_Title: El Jeneral Don Luis de la Cruz
Creator: Gil de Castro, José
Description: The exact date of this painting is uncertain. De la Cruz was an explorer, and active in the independence movement, being a close friend of O'Higgins. He was part of the expeditionary force to Peru in 1820. The caption on the painting reads, 'Trabajó constantamente por la libertad de la patria'. Colonial Exhibition num. 69.

Name_Title: Retrato del Secretario de la Capitanía Jeneral Don Júdas Tadeo Reyes
Creator: Gil de Castro, José
Description: The painting dates from 1827. He was the last head of the inquisition in Chile. The caption reads, 'Retrato al óleo del señor don Judas Tadeo de Reyes i Borda, natural de Santiago de Chile, oficial real i por 32 años secretario de la presidencia i capitanía jeneral de este reino. Retratado de 59 años de edad: murió a los 70 años 4 meses i 8 dias el 18 de noviembre de 1827. Trabajado por José Jil, pintor peruano, el año de 1818'. Colonial Exhibition num. 64.

Name_Title: Retrato del Secretario de la Capitanía Jeneral Don Júdas Tadeo Reyes
Creator: Bourgeois, Amelia
Description: The painting was done in 1873, at the request of Benjamín Vicuña Mackenna, for the Colonial Exhibition. Bourgeois was at the time a student at the Academia de Pintura. Caption reads, 'Jeneral de Artilleria, mediocre militar, majistrado bien intencionado pero débil. Su victoria de Rancagua le dió el mando del pais i su derrota de Maipo le causó la muerte, pues falleció en Panamá de pesar i de dolencias al regresar a España en 1878'.

Name_Title: El momento supremo - Batalla de Maipu
Creator: Subercaseaux, Pedro
Description: The painting was done in 1904 and exhibited in the Salon de Bellas Artes the same year. Catalogue notes, 'Con dificultad se ha visto un ataque más bravo, más rápido i más sostenido, i jams se vió una resistencia más vigorosa, más firme i más tenaz'.

Name_Title: Retrato del Fiscal Perez de Uriondo' and 'Retrato de la Esposa del Fiscal Uriondo
Creator: Anon.
Description: Probably 18th century portraits, exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exposition (num.s 101 and 102). The pair were purchased in 1911 by the Museo Histórico Nacional for $300, from Mauro Pando, an antiques dealer. The caption on the Fiscal's portrait reads, 'Retrato del señor don Joaquin Perez de Uriondo i Martierena del Barranco, Colejial de la Real (illegible) de San Juan de la ciudad de la Plata de Consejo de S.M. i su fiscal de la Real Audiencia de Chile, i caballero cruzado de la distinguida órden de Cárlos III. Hijo lejítimo del señor don Joaquin Pérez de Uriondo i Murguia del Consejo de S.M., su Oidor i Alcalde de Corte de la Real Audiencia de Charcas, i de la señora doña Antonia Prodenco Martierena del Barranco i Fernandes Campero'. The caption on his wife's portrait reads, 'Retrato de la señora doña Ines Vicenta Menendez Valdes de Cornellana Flenexal i Ruiz de Noriega. Nació en la cuidad de Valladolid. Hija lejítima de don Manuel Menendez Valdes de Cornellana Flenexal Ruis de Noriega, desposada con el seño

Name_Title: Campaña del Desierto. Cacique Millamain (Buitre de Oro) sometido en 1882, y mujeres de la tribu en sus tolderías a inmediaciones de Norquín
Creator: Encina, Carlos and Moreno, Edgardo
Description: Photograph from the album of engineers and topographers Encina's and Moreno's expedition to the so-called 'Territorio del Triangulo' between the Neuquén and Limay rivers and the Andes, in today's province of Neuquén, Argentina, 1883. Their expedition coincided with the 'Campaña de los Andes' of the Argentine army under the Generals Villegas and Vintter, hunting down the last resistent indigenous communities from Patagonia and the southern Pampas, who had taken refuge in the Cordilleras, despite one of the cruellest winters in memory. The last of them surrendered in 1884, their tribes being deported to serve as household slaves or plantation workers in Buenos Aires and Tucumán, in a genocidal politics of systematic 'ethnic cleansing'. Millamain was a pehuenche chief with allegiance to Reunque Curá, brother of Calfucurá, the long-time leader of the Araucanian Federation of Salinas Grandes, who had surrendered to the army the year before Encina's and Moreno's expedition, and was serving in military and intelligence missions against other groups in the vicinity. This 'family snapshot' that shows him, in military uniform, amongst his wives and family, is one of the last pictures of Araucanian/Pampa culture prior to its destruction.

Name_Title: Batalla de Tuyutí, 14 de marzo de 1867, los batallones 4 y 6 de línea inician la batalla
Creator: López, Cándido
Description: Large-scale painting of the battle of Tuyutí between the forces of the Triple Alliance and the Paraguayan army, 1867 - López's oniric depictions of the Paraguayan war are amongst the strangest and the most important bodies of painting produced in 19th-century Latin America. López had participated in the war himself, and lost his right arm in the battle of Tuyutí. Previously an ambitious, if highly conventional, painter, he now took to what he saw as mere documentation, and commemoration, of the events, claiming only historical but no aesthetic value for his work. When first exposed, the paintings were accompanied by short memories of the battles penned by López himself.

Name_Title: Un episodio de la fiebre amarilla en Buenos Aires
Creator: Blanes, Juan Manuel
Description: Famous painting depicting hygienists Manuel Argerich and Roque Pérez inspecting a victim of the yellow fever epidemy. The painting, which had already been sold by the artist to a private collector, was exposed in the Teatro Colón following the epidemy of 1872, causing a sensation of unseen proportions and eventually obliging the government to solicit another copy from Blanes.

Creator: unkown
Description: The Faculty of Medicine's library, illustration taken from 'La Universidad Nacional de Buenos Aires, 1821-1910' (Buenos Aires, 1910). This library had been founded in 1863 on initiative of Montes de Oca. In 1864 it held 804 volumes, in 1875 this number had risen to 1123 bound volumes and 200 fascicles. It was established at the locale depicted on the photograph in 1897, enjoying the reputation of being the best specialized library in South America.

Name_Title: Biblioteca de la Facultad de Derecho
Creator: unkown
Description: The library of the Faculty of Law, illustration taken from 'La Universidad Nacional de Buenos Aires, 1821-1910' (Buenos Aires, 1910). Founded in 1885 by Juan María Gutiérrez, this library held approximately 30.000 volumes in 1910, of which 14.000 had been acquired between 1902 and 1910. The first catalogue was published in 1898.

Name_Title: **Chegada da Fragata Constituição ao Rio de Janeiro
Creator: de Martino, Eduardo
Description: Autor de quadros qui registraram os feitos da marhina brasileira, este pintor italiano especializou-se em temas navais e de carácter histórico.  Após sua estada no Brasil transferiu-se para Londres onde foi nomeado pintor da Corte.  Neste quadro o autor procura reconstituir a chegada, em 3 de setembro de 1843, da fragata Constitução, capitãnia da divisão da esquadra imperial que foi buscar, em Nápoles, a Princesa do Reino das Duas Sicílias, Dona Teresa Cristina, que se tornaria, ao casar com o joven D. Pedro II, a terceira imperatriz do Brasil.  Destaca-se no primeiro plano a Galeota Imperial, que pertencera a D. João VI e transportou a nova Imperatriz a cais.  A chegada dos noivas era revestida de grande aparato e entusiasmo, com festas que duravam vários dias.  A Corte era especialmente decorada para estas ocasiões.

Name_Title: Plaque, carta de despedida
Description: A contemporary photograph of the plaque, reproducing part of Claude Gay's farewell letter, at the front of the Museo Nacional de Historia Natural. The plaque reads, 'Por ahora me limito a recomendarle encarecidamente el museo de Santiago, que me veo como el resulato mas invaluble (?) de mi feliz residencia en esta republica. Aunque es mui nuevo y aunque casi no ha ocasionado el gobierno mas gastos que en de los estantes, puedo asegurar que no seria depreciado en (?) grandes ciudades de Europa, y que no encontraria su igual en ninguna de las republicas de origen español. Creo que es un establecimiento que hace honor al pais i que merece la atencion del gobierno y de us.'

Name_Title: Retrato del Fiscal Perez de Uriondo' and 'Retrato de la Esposa del Fiscal Uriondo
Creator: Anon.
Description: Probably 18th century portraits, exhibited in the 1873 Colonial Exposition (num.s 101 and 102). The pair were purchased in 1911 by the Museo Histórico Nacional for $300, from Mauro Pando, an antiques dealer. The caption on the Fiscal's portrait reads, 'Retrato del señor don Joaquin Perez de Uriondo i Martierena del Barranco, Colejial de la Real (illegible) de San Juan de la ciudad de la Plata de Consejo de S.M. i su fiscal de la Real Audiencia de Chile, i caballero cruzado de la distinguida órden de Cárlos III. Hijo lejítimo del señor don Joaquin Pérez de Uriondo i Murguia del Consejo de S.M., su Oidor i Alcalde de Corte de la Real Audiencia de Charcas, i de la señora doña Antonia Prodenco Martierena del Barranco i Fernandes Campero'. The caption on his wife's portrait reads, 'Retrato de la señora doña Ines Vicenta Menendez Valdes de Cornellana Flenexal i Ruiz de Noriega. Nació en la cuidad de Valladolid. Hija lejítima de don Manuel Menendez Valdes de Cornellana Flenexal Ruis de Noriega, desposada con el seño

These picture-cards, with their nostalgic evocation of urban slavery, became extremely popular in the late 1880s, especially after the definitive abolition of slavery in 1888.

Name_Title: 500 mil reis
Creator: Pedro II
Description: Imperial bank note depicting Emperor Pedro II

Name_Title: Cartas-bilhetes
Creator: Pedro II
Description: Stamped post cards depicting Emperor Pedro II

Name_Title: Portrait of D. Pedro II
Creator: Pedro II
Description: Studio portrait of Pedro II a year before his overthrow by the military

Name_Title: Portrait of Antônio Carlos Gomes
Creator: Gomes, Antônio Carlos
Description: Studio portrait of the Brazilian composer (Campinas 1836-Belém 1896), author of 'O Guarani', the opera adapted from José de Alencar´s indianist novel. Gomes studied in Italy thanks to a grant from the Emperor. 'O Guarani' enjoyed a triumphant opening at Milan's Scala theatre in 1870.

Name_Title: Primeira missa no Brasil
Creator: Meireles de Lima, Vitor
Description: First version of Meireles's classic painting

Name_Title: Estudo para o panorama de Rio de Janeiro (entrada da Barra)
Creator: Meireles de Lima, Vitor
Description: One in a series of panoramic views of Rio de Janeiro, a popular genre topic at the time. Meireles exhibited another Rio panorama, painted in collaboration with the Belgian Henri Langerock, a long-time resident in Brazil, at the Paris World's Fair of 1889.

Name_Title: Batalha das Guararapes
Creator: Meireles de Lima, Vitor
Description: Detail of one of Meireles's most succesful battle paintings, depicting a clash between the Dutch and the Portuguese and Creole militias near Olinda (Pernambuco) in 1648. Meireles had undertaken extensive fieldwork at the original sites, and had worked on the painting for almost six years, only to face widespread criticism for its lack of movement and realism, when displaying the work at the Salon of 1880 (where it was shown next to Pedro Américo's equally influential 'Batalha do Avaí')

Name_Title: D. Pedro na abertura da Assembléia Geral
Creator: Figueiredo e Melo, Pedro Américo de
Description: Painting representing Emperor Pedro II during his throne speech at the inauguration of the parliamentary period, on May 3rd, 1872. Several imperial notables can be seen on the lower left side surrounding D. Pedro's platform, among them the Visconde de Abaeté (president of the Senade), the Duque de Caxias (military commander during the Paraguayan war) , or the Visconde do Rio Branco, at that time minister of the treasury, who would later on become the most influential figure in Brazilian foreign politics of the late 19th century. On the balcony, .the Empress Teresa Cristina, the Princess Isabel and her husband, the Conde d'Eu.

Name_Title: Moema
Creator: Meireles de Lima, Vitor
Description: Inspired by the indianist poem 'Caramuru', by Santa Rita Durão, a tragic story of the unresponded love of an indian girl for a Portuguese adventurer, this work was first exposed at the 1866 Fine Arts Exhibition, where critics accused Meireles of having plagiarized Eugene Isabey's romantic piece 'Virginia morte sur la plage'.
Copyright_Owner: Museu de Arte de São Paulo

Name_Title: Estudo de anatomia para <Tiradentes 	Esquartejado>
Creator: Figueiredo e Melo, Pedro Américo de
Description: Anatomic study for a historical painting depicting the execution of Tiradentes, the Mineiro conspirator and republican hero. Pedro Américo whose work had been closely associated with the Second Empire (see his portrait of the Emperor inaugurating the parliament in 1872) with this and other works of republican subject matter sought to gain sympathies among the new regime.

Name_Title: Estudo de anatomia para <Tiradentes 	Esquartejado>
Creator: Figueiredo e Melo, Pedro Américo de
Description: Anatomic study for a historical painting depicting the execution of Tiradentes, the Mineiro conspirator and republican hero. Pedro Américo whose work had been closely associated with the Second Empire (see his portrait of the Emperor inaugurating the parliament in 1872) with this and other works of republican subject matter sought to gain sympathies among the new regime.

Creator: Figueiredo e Melo, Pedro Américo de
Description: Anatomic study for a historical painting depicting the execution of Tiradentes, the Mineiro conspirator and republican hero. Pedro Américo whose work had been closely associated with the Second Empire (see his portrait of the Emperor inaugurating the parliament in 1872) with this and other works of republican subject matter sought to gain sympathies among the new regime.

Name_Title: Redenção do Cam
Creator: Brocos y Gomes, Modesto
Description: This emblematic picture of the ideology of 'branuqeamento', or 'whitening', of the Brazilian population, was later reproduced on the cover of João Baptista de Lacerda´s -the director of the National Museum- contribution to the 1. International Congress on Race, celebrated in 1911 at Geneva, Switzerland. The speech was entitled 'Sur le métis au Brésil', and carried the subtitle "Le nègre passant au blanc, à la troisième génération, par l´éffet du croisement des races"

Name_Title: Primeira missa no Brasil
Creator: Meireles de Lima, Vitor
Description: The final version of Meireles's painting, the result of several years'  work while on a government grant in Europe, relied among other literary sources on the chronicles of Pedro Vaz de Caminha and on Ferdinand Denis's History of Brazilian literature. First exposed in Paris in 1859 and, following small modifications, in 1860 at Rio de Janeiro, 'Primeira Missa' in 1876 was acquired by the imperial government and, alongside two battle scenes from the Paraguayan war, exhibited at the Philadelphia World's Fair.

Name_Title: Alegoria à lei do Ventre Livre
Creator: Bressac, A. D.
Description: Bronze statue celebrating the 'Law of the Free Womb', also known as 'Rio-Branco law' after the then prime minister, which prohibited the enslavement of newborn children, even though their parents were slaves

Name_Title: Rio Madeira
Creator: Rochet, Louis
Description: Bronze statue that was to form part of an ensemble of idealized, allegorical figures of natives symbolizing Brazil's great rivers, and displayed around the pedestal of the equestrian monument to Pedro I, erected in 1865 on today's Tiradentes square in central Rio de Janeiro. These ornamental figures had been designed by the Brazilian painter José Maximiliano Mafra (1823'1908), but were eventually commissioned to Rochet (1813-1978), a reknowned French genre artist, who crafted the original casts in Paris, copies of which were then taken in Rio.

Name_Title: Resposta de Tiradentes à comutação da pena de morte dos inconfidentes
Creator: de Faria, Leopoldino
Description: Historical painting depicting the moment the death verdict against Tiradentes, and minor punishments against his fellow Mineiro conspirators is pronounced. The painting, one in a series of works commemorating the events of 1789, was commissioned to Faria, a reknowned genre painter, by the council of Ouro Preto, in a bid to underscore the Mineiro region's deep republican traditions.

Name_Title: Retrato de André Pinto Rebouças
Creator: Bernardelli, Rodolfo
Description: A graduate in engineering from the military academy, Rebouças (1838-1898) was heavily involved in the refashioning of Rio de Janeiro and other great engineering works of the late Second Empire. An active abolitionist, Rebouças continued supporting the monarchy after 1889 and committed suicide while living in exile in Portugal in 1898.

Name_Title: Paisagem
Creator: Pagani, João Baptista
Description: Pagani, the son of Genovese immigrants, had arrived in Brazil as a child. A student of João Maximiliano Mafra and Vitor Meireles at the imperial academy of art, he participated at the Fine Arts Exhibitions of 1876,1884 and 1890, obtaining a Grand and a Second Gold Medal. IAt the Exhibition of 1893, some of his works were displayed in hommage to the painter, who had died in 1891.

Name_Title: Engenho de Mandioca
Creator: Brocos y Gomes, Modesto
Description: Brocos (1852-1936), the son of Spanish immigrants,  had come to Brazil in 1872 to study at the imperial academy with Vitor Meireles. His most reknowned works deal with topics of race and popular culture.

Name_Title: Natureza morta
Creator: Silva, Estevão
Description: A black painter of poor background, Silva (ca. 1845-1891) specialized in still lifes, a genre in which he is regarded as the finest Brazilian artist of his time. He had been a student of Vitor Meireles, Jules Le Chevreuil e Agostinho José da Mota at the imperial academy,  and was linked to some of the landscape artists of the Grimm group. Silva held a position as professor at the Liceu de Artes e Oficios, Rio de Janeiro.

Name_Title: A palavra para os sordo mudos
Creator: Pereira da Silva, Oscar
Description: First exposed at the Salon of 1893 under the title 'O Dr. Meneses Vieira dando uma leção de linguagem' (Dr Meneses Vieira holding a language class'), this painting by Pereira da Silva (1867-1939) is an odd tribute to the spirit of medical reform cut loose by the research and medical campaigns of Chagas and Cruz, among others. Pereira da Soilva, thanks to a government grant, had studied in Paris with Léon Gerôule and Léon Bonnet, before returning to Brasil in 1896. He taught at São Paulo's Ginasio do Estado and at the Escola de Belas Artes, was a frequent designer of stage decorations at the Teatro Municipal, and painted some of the interior decoration of the Museu Paulista.

Name_Title: Habitação na raiz da Serra da Estrela
Creator: Pinto Bandeira, Antônio Rafael
Description: Born at Niterói, Pinto Bandeira began his studies at the imperial art academy in 1879, after which he taught for several years at the Liceu de Artes e Oficios of Salvador da Bahia. Close to the Grimm group of landscape artists, on returning to Rio he participated at the Exhibitions of 1884 and 1890, and obtained the Prêmio Imperatriz do Brazil in 1885. In 1896 he committed suicide by jumping off the ferry Niterói-Rio.

Name_Title: Paisagem de Niterói
Creator: Monteiro, Antônio Firmino
Description: Although previously reknowned for his historical genre paintings, Monteiro (1855-1888) on returning from his last journey to Europe started to venture into landscape painting. A student of  Vitor Meireles,  José da Mota and Zeferino da Costa at the imperial art academy, Monteiro participated at the General Exhibitions of 1884, 1885 and 1887, obtaining a Second Class Gold Medal.

Name_Title: Paisagem de Sabará
Creator: Caron, Hipólito Boaventura
Description: Caron (1862-1892) had began his studies at the imperial art academy in 1880, becoming a professor for drawing at Rio de Janeiro's Liceu de Artes e Oficios in 1882. In 1884, year in which he obtains a Gold Medal at the General Exhibition, he resigns from the academy to join the Grimm group of landscape painters at Niterói, onde participa das excursões do grupo Grimm. Having travelled to Europe in 1885-88, he settles in his native Minas Gerais, where in 1892 he dies from yellow fever. This mineiro landscape is one of his last works.

Name_Title: Morro da Viúva
Creator: França Júnior, Joaquim José da
Description: A graduate in Letters and Humanities from Rio's Colégio Pedro II, França Júnior, (1858-1890)  started a degree in laws at the Facultade de Direito, São Paulo, before dedicating himself to painting. From 1882 he studied with Georg Grimm at the imperial art academy. This work depicts a peak in the Serra dos Orgãos near Rio de Janeiro.

Name_Title: Canto de Praia
Creator: Parreiras, Antonio
Description: Born at Niterói where he would spend most of his life, Parreiras (1860-1937) entered the imperial art academy in 1883, where he studied with Johann Georg Grimm, the German landscape painter who had been contracted in 1882 as interim professor, and who would become a major influence on a generation of Brazilian painters to become known as 'The Grimm group'. One of its chief exponents, Parreiras, after a brief stay at Venice in 1888, settled at his native Niterói, also the groups 'headquarters'.

Name_Title: Os buritis de Parnamirim
Creator: Tellas Júnior, Jerônimo José
Description: Born in Recife, Tellas Júnior (1851-1914) went to Rio Grande do Sul to take painting lessons with Eduardo de Martino, an Italian naval painter who had been commissioned for a large series of images by the Brazilian army. Tellas went on to Rio to study with Agostinho José da Mota, to eventually obtain a teaching post at the Liceu de Artes e Oficios of his native Recife. The present work depicts a landscape of the interior of Pernambuco.

Name_Title: Iracema
Creator: de Medeiros, José María
Description: Along with Rodolfo Amoedo's 'O Último Tamoio', Augusto Rodrigues Duarte's 'Exéquias de Atalá', and Vitor Meireles's 'Moema', this adaptation of José de Alencar's homonymous 'Ceará legend' must be counted among the most significant indianist works. Medeiros, born on the Azores, had initially started a career as bookbinder ar the Liceu de Artes e Oficios, of which he would later become a professor. A student of Vitor Meireles at the imperial art academy, Medeiros from 1882 held the academy's chair for figurative design. The present work was aming the favourites of Emperor Pedro II, who granted Medeiros the title of 'Official of the Order of Roses'.

Name_Title: Moisés e Jocabed
Creator: Figueiredo e Melo, Pedro Américo de
Description: The foremost Brazilian painter in the 19th century along with Vitor Miereles, Pedro Américo (1843-1905) had done his first drawings as a member of Louis Jacques Brunet's expedition to the north-east. After studying at the imperial art academy, of which he would later become a professor, with Manuel de Araújo Porto-Alegre, he first travelled to Europe on an imperial grant, settling subsequently in Paris and Florence. The present painting depicts Moses's mother Jocabed who, not being able to hide her son any longer from Herodes's soldiers, takes him to the river, where he will be left in a basket.

Name_Title: Archivos do Museu Nacional
Creator: Netto, Ladislau
Description: Table of contents of a special issue of the museum's journal, dedicated entirely to archaeological and anthropological topics, in the wake of the Anthropological Exhibition of 1882.

Name_Title: Archivos do Museu Nacional
Creator: Netto, Ladislau
Description: Table of contents of a special issue of the museum's journal, dedicated entirely to archaeological and anthropological topics, in the wake of the Anthropological Exhibition of 1882.

Name_Title: Retrato da familia imperial (detail)
Creator: Anonymous
Description: An amateur's portrait of the imperial family, probably copied from an official photograoph of the sort that circulated as postcards and other souvenirs in the 1880s

Name_Title: Retrato da familia imperial
Creator: Anonymous
Description: An amateur's portrait of the imperial family, probably copied from an official photograoph of the sort that circulated as postcards and other souvenirs in the 1880s

Name_Title: Alegoria da República
Creator: Villares, Décio
Description: Undated sketch for an allegory of the Brazilian republic by Décio Villares, a fierce republican and positivist artist, in an attermpt to transpose onto Brazil the symbology of the French revolution (female allegories, Jacobine caps, etc.)

Name_Title: Tiradentes
Creator: Villares, Décio
Description: Portrait of Tiradentes, the Republican 'martyr' who was condemned to death in the ill-fated mineiro conspiracy of 1789. The resemblances to religious images of Christ and the martyrs are particularly obvious in this version, a clear attempt to create a 'civic religion'.

Name_Title: Alegoria à Lei do Ventre Livre (detail)
Creator: Bressac, A. D.
Description: Bronze statue celebrating the 'Law of the Free Womb', also known as 'Rio-Branco law' after the then prime minister, which prohibited the enslavement of new-born children, even though their parents were slaves

Name_Title: Vapor Marqués de Olinda no porto de Assunção
Creator: de Martino, Eduardo
Description: A Brazilian battleship anchors off the port of Asunción, on Paraná river, during the Paraguayan war (1865-1870). De Martino, a reknowned naval painter, was commissioned by the Brazilian navy to paint a series of works highlighting the force's role in the campaign.

Name_Title: Estudo para <O descobrimento do Brasil>
Creator: de Figueiredo e Melo, Francisco Aurélio
Description: Sketch for a great historical painting. Aurélio de Figueiredo (1854-1916), a native of Pernambuco, was among the protagonists of the romantic movement. Even though his work is often eclipsed by the more grandiloquent and theatrical gesture of his older brother, Pedro Américo, today's critics value his superior sense of colour.

Name_Title: Passagem do Chaco (detail)
Creator: de Figueiredo e Melo, Pedro Américo
Description: Painting depicting a decisive move of the Brazilian army during the Paraguayan war, the 'passage of the Chaco' in 1867 in order to catch the Paraguayan troops by surprise. Pedro Américo participated in the Paraguayan campaign himself and gathered materials for some of his major battle paintings on site.

Name_Title: Passagem do Chaco
Creator: de Figueiredo e Melo, Pedro Américo
Description: Painting depicting a decisive move of the Brazilian army during the Paraguayan war, the 'passage of the Chaco' in 1867 in order to catch the Paraguayan troops by surprise. Pedro Américo participated in the Paraguayan campaign himself and gathered materials for some of his major battle paintings on site.

Name_Title: Tipos das ruas
Creator: Araújo Lopes, Erotides Américo de
Description: A series of picturesque figurines carved in wood by a Bahian popular artist. They were popular as household pieces of memorabilia amongst a local upper class nostalgic for an idealized imperial past.

Name_Title: Bust of Deodoro da Fonseca
Creator: Villares, Décio
Description: Deodoro da Fonseca, a patriarchal figure in the Brazilian army and 'hero' of the Paraguayan war, commanded the military insurgency of 1889 which ended the Brazilian empire. Deodoro's agreement to head the move, despite his conservative views, eventually secured its backing by the military.

Es del bajo pueblo; ha sido vendedor de diarios, cuartereador de carros y vago. Tiene relación con ladrones peligrosos y estos tienen confianza en su discreción."

Creator: Silva Paranhos Júnior, José Maria da
Description: Photograph illustrating the map ‘Estados Unidos do Brazil.  Mappa desenhado e gravado sob a direção do Snr. Barão do Rio-Branco, escala 1 : 5.000.000’. The image shows the former Imperial Palace at São Cristóvão, Rio de Janeiro, which, following the overthrow of the monarchy in 1889, served as preliminary pariament during the Constituent Assembly, and from 1892 as seat of the National Museum, formerly on the central Sant'Anna Square.

The image shows a panoramic view over the city of Rio de Janeiro and Guanabara Bay.

Name_Title: Egreja de S. José, Ministerio da agricultura
Creator: Silva Paranhos Júnior, José Maria da
Description: Illustrations on map ‘Estados Unidos do Brazil.  Mappa desenhado e gravado sob a direção do Snr. Barão do Rio-Branco, escala 1 : 5.000.000’. Its editor, José Maria da Silva Paranhos Júnior, who kept using his nobility title even after the Republican regime had formally abolished these, was the architect of Brazil's foreign policy in the late nineteenth and early twentieth century, one of whose goals was the obtention of lands through border disputes submitted to international arbitage. Paranhos's publishing career (during which he also edited a sumptuous collection of essays and photographs exhibited at the Paris World's Fair of 1889) was an instrumental part of this strategy of woeing the transatlantic powers to Brazil's cause.

Name_Title: Carta da República dos Estados Unidos do Brazil (Detail)
Creator: Serzedello Correa, Innocencio
Description: Southern section of a map of the Brazilian Republic depicting the border with the 'Estdo Oriental' (Uruguay). Colour and shading suggest that this 'state' still belongs to Brazil, which had in fact annexed in immediately after secession from the Portuguese motherland as the 'Provincia Cisplatina', causing a war with Argentina in 1825-28 that was only resolved through a bilateral treaty patrocinated by Britain, which declared the 'Oriental Republic of Uruguay' a neutral buffer state. Nevertheless, the country was still often referred to in Imperial cartography as belonging to Brazil, a tradition that is here tacitally taken over by the Republic succeeding the imperial state.

Name_Title: Neologia e neographia brasileira
Creator: Araripe Júnior, Tristão de Alencar de
Publisher: Boletim da Sociedade de Geographia do Rio de Janeiro
Description: Cover page of an article published in the Journal of Rio de Janeiro's Geographical Society, which argues the need for a new, proper and autonomous, geographical vocabulary. Araripe Júnior was one of Brazil's most influential cultural critics of the late nineteenth century, particularly renowned for his polemic with Sylvio Romero and others, in which he defended the importance of the influence of the environment on the formation of an individual and collective character over that of race and inheritance.

Creator: Mello Morães Filho, Alexandre José
Description: Illustration from 'Festas e tradições populares', an anthology of Brazilian popular festivals and customs compilated by Alexandre José Mello Morães Filho. The image shows a black slave in the stalls, a means of punishment which is here documented as 'traditional custom'.

Name_Title: Capoeira alfaiate
Creator: Junius, Flumen
Description: Illustration from 'Festas e tradições populares', an anthology of Brazilian popular festivals and customs compilated by Alexandre José Mello Morães Filho. The image is almost certainly a print made after a photographic 'carte de visite', the kind of which became fashionable in late nineteenth-century Brazil as a souvenir of the bygone, idyllic days of slavery.

Name_Title: Relatório apresentado a S. Ex. o Sr. Ministro da Industria, Viação e Obras Publicas (Cover)
Creator: Cruls, Luiz
Publisher: H. Lombaerts / C. Impressores do Observatorio
Description: The Cruls expedition was commissioned in 1892 with outlining the area for a new federal district in the heartland -or 'Planalto Central'- of the Brazilian republic, which would become the site of the new federal capital. The project was soon put on hold due to insufficient funding, and only taken up again under the presidency of Juscelino Kubitschek in 1956, resulting in the construction of Brasília, inaugurated in 1960.

Name_Title: **Embarque do meteorito Bendegó na Estrada de Ferro Prolongamento de Bahia pelos engenheiros que o foram buscar no interior inóspito da Bahia
Creator: Antunes
Description: Antunes, Embarque do meteorito Bendegó na Estrada de Ferro Prolongamento de Bahia pelos engenheiros que o foram buscar no interior inóspito da Bahia (Bahia 1887), albumen 15,5 x 21,5 cm, Coleção Gilberto Ferrez.  The Bendegó meteorite had been discovered in 18?? In the interior of Bahia state, but had not been removed before despite attempts on behalf of the National Musuem of Rio de Janeiro due to its exorbitant weight.  Only with the extension of railway technology could the transport be effectuated.  The meteorite would arrive at Rio de Janeiro after the republican coup, and subsequently be exposed in the entrance hall of the Museum at São Cristóvao, the former Imperial Palace.  Illustration taken from Rubens Fernandes Júnior & Pedro Corrêa do Lago (eds.), O século XIX na fotografia brasileira:  coleção Pedro Corrêa do Lago.  Brasilia:  Francisco Alves, 2001.

Name_Title: **Cachoeira de Paulo Afonso
Creator: Stahl, Augusto
Description: Augusto Stahl, Cachoeira de Paulo Afonso (Pernambuco, 1860), albumen 25,8 x 55,6 cm.  Large-scale lanscape panorama composed of two photographs, which Stahl dedicated to the Emperor Pedro II.  One of the first photographic landscapes on paper (rather than using the more familiar daguerrotype), in the making of this image the slightly lighter machinery permitted the photographer to approach his subject more closely, yet it also required quick and skilfull handling of wet negatives.  Stahl had asked a young black local to pose fro him on the rocks closest to the waterfall –an extremely dangerous stunt – to give an idea of proportion.  The image was plagiated in 1868 by Augusto Riedel in his album recording the Duke of Saxony’s journey across Brazil, inserting the figure of a white leisure traveller contemplating the falls instead of Stahl’s young black.  Illustration taken from Bia Corrêa do Lago, Augusto Stahl, obra completa em Pernambuco e Rio de Janeiro.  Rio de Janeiro:  Capivara, 2001.

Name_Title: **Negro de frente, de perfil e de costas
Creator: Stahl, Augusto
Description: Augusto Stahl, Negro de frente, de perfil e de costas (Rio de Janeiro 1865), albumen 21 x 28 cm.  Picture from a series of physiological studies Stahl took on request from Louis Agassiz, who was travelling Brazil at the head of the Thayer expedition (named after its sponsor, a US philanthropist), whose principal objective was the study of fish from the Amazonian and São Francisco basins.  Agassiz published an account of the journey, co-scripted with his wife, Elizabeth Carey, which was illustrated with several lithographies reproducing photographs by Stahl (cf. A Journey in Brazil, by Prof. And Mrs. Louis Agassiz.  Boston:  Ticknor & Fields, 1868).  Among these were four portraits of female slaves and two views of Rio de Janeiro’s botanical garden.  Also on request from Agassiz, Stahl took a series of photographs of blacks and Chinese immigrants, all of which repeated the standardised front, profile and rear view common to physiological photography of the time.  None of these images were included in the book on Brazil, but rather seemed to have been taken for a forthcoming comparative study of the human races.  Agassiz, however, included physiological typologies of the races in his travel book, such as this characterisation of blacks:  “of long arms, the Negroes are generally slim; they have long legs and a relatively short torso; the shoulderblades are long and stand close to one another, the back is slightly wrinkled and slender; the hands disproportionably slim, with the interdigital furrows more prolonged than in any other race."  Illustration taken from Bia Corrêa do Lago, Augusto Stahl, obra completa em Pernambuco e Rio de Janeiro.  Rio de Janeiro:  Capivara, 2001.

Name_Title: Andrés Lamas en su escritorio
Creator: Lamas, Andrés
Description: Photograph of Andrés Lamas, antiquarian, historian, geographer and collector, in his home at Buenos Aires, surrounded by objects of his collection of historical memorabilia from the River Plate. Lamas was one of the instigators of the creation of the Argentine National Historical Museum and a co-organiser of the historical exhibition at the Exposición Continental of 1882. He was also principally involved in the re-organisation of state patrimony after 1880, when the assets of archives and museums had to be re-distributed between the federal state and the government of the province of Buenos Aires. (Museo Mitre, Buenos Aires)

Name_Title: **Martírio de Tiradentes
Creator: de Figueiredo, Aurélio
Description: Representaçao idealizada do enforcamento de Joaquim José da Silva Xavier, chamando ‘O Tiradentes’, um dos conspiradores envolvidos na Inconfidência Miniera de 1789.  Este movimiento foi uma tentativa de tornar a região que abrangia Rio de Janeiro e Minas Gerais numa república independente.  Seus participantes eram membros das elites mineiras descontentes com as medidas fiscais e repressivas que vinham sendo tomadas pelas autoridades portugueses.

Name_Title: Album de vistas fotográficas de La Plata
Creator: Anonymous
Description: Caption reads: Alegoría de la fundación from Anonymous, Album de vistas fotográficas de La Plata desde su fundación, noviembre 1882, hasta agosto de 1885. The city of La Plata was founded in 1882 as the new  capital of Buenos Aires province, following the federalisation of Buenos Aires city as national capital in 1880, its name having been proposed by José Hernández, the author of 'Martín Fierro' (1872-79), the national poem.

Name_Title: Le Brésil en 1889
Creator: Santa-Anna Néry, F. J. de
Description: Volume compilated on the occasion of the Universal Exhibition of 1889. The facsimil library holds the following chapters: "L´Empire du Brésil à l´Exposition Universelle de 1889"; "Introduction: Le Brésil actuel" par 	F.J.de Santa-Anna Néry; chap.XVI, "Immigration" par S.da Silva-Prado; "Table des matières"; 	map "Amérique du Sud"; chap.XXI, "Sciences.Le Muséum National" par M. le Conseiller 	Ladislau Netto; chap. XX, "Littérature" par F. J. de Santa-Anna Néry
